post_text: The Nokomis FFA Chapter will be showcased this weekend, September 12-13, 2020, on “This Week In AgriBusiness”, a weekly, one-hour television agri-news program hosted by two of the country’s most well-known farm broadcasters Max Armstrong and Orion Samuelson. The Nokomis FFA Chapter Tribute will include information about the Chapter’s history, activities and community service. It also includes an interview with Nora Patton, as well as several photos of the students and their participation in chapter activities. Viewers can see the Nokomis FFA Chapter Tribute during “This Week In AgriBusiness” which is aired on RFD-TV, a 24-hour television network for rural America. RFD-TV is carried on Dish Network channel 231 and on DirecTV channel 345, as well as a number of other cable systems. “This Week In AgriBusiness” airs three times on RFD-TV throughout the weekend. Broadcast times are 7:00a.m. on Saturday; 5:00a.m. and 9:30p.m. on Sundays; (Central Time Zone). #NOKOPROUD

post_text: Beginning Monday, August 24, 2020, all Nokomis public and private schools will dismiss students at 2:30 p.m. for the entire 1st quarter. This is to allow our teachers and support staff to make positive and meaningful contact with our remote learners. Also, Friday, September 4, 2020 will be a Remote Learning Planning Day, which means students will not be in attendance that day. This will allow teachers and support staff to receive professional development on new technology and remote learning resources. Thank you for your cooperation.

Illinois High School Association (IHSA)
April 16 at 12:05 PM ·

💡💡💡💡💡💡💡💡💡💡💡💡
On Friday night, IHSA schools throughout Illinois will turn on their lights as a part of #LightsForTheFight to show support for their senior students, as well as for all the healthcare workers, first responders, & all other essential workers on the frontlines of the pandemic.

📰 Learn more about the initiative ⬇️⬇️⬇️
https://www.ihsa.org/IHSA-State/IHSA-State-Articles/ihsa-schools-turn-on-lights-for-the-fight-to-show-support-for-seniors-covid-heroes

post_text: Nokomis - Get counted! Make sure to participate in the 2020 Census. Check it out at my2020census.gov. Funding to our community and schools depend on the Census. Get counted! #NOKOPROUD
shared_text:
MCEDC-Montgomery County Economic Development Corporation
March 27 at 12:35 PM ·

MCEDC will be providing 2020 Census updates. Before the Covid-19 epidemic we new a strong response to the Census would be highly important for funding to our county. Now it will be CRITICAL as the economic impact of this virus will last much longer then the quarantine. Nokomis, you are doing pretty well with your responses and they are slowly climbing, but now is the time to step it up and get counted!

If you have not participated, please do so today via the link in the comments.

I encourage all Montgomery County residents to participate, but below we have included numbers for Nokomis. Watch for updates from our other communities.

post_text: The Redskins defeated Hillsboro Saturday night. We remembered Coach Kimbro’s 401-500 wins. The 02-03 team finished with a 24-9 record. They won the Morrisonville Tournament and a Regional Championship. The 03-04 team finished with a 15-15 record. The 04-05 team finished with a 27-5 record. They won the Morrisonville Tournament and a Regional Championship. The 05-06 team finished with a record of 30-3. They won the Conference, the Morrisonville Tournament, The Litchfield Tournament, a Regional and Sectional Championship. One player hit the 1000 point mark during these 100 wins. Blake Johnson from the class of 2006 finished with 1118 points. Coach Kimbro won his 500th game on February 7th, 2006 against Girard. 🔴⚫️🏀 #NOKOPROUD

Career day at North

We would also like to thank North teachers, Darci Harrison, Lacy Suslee, and Emily Chumley for their help in marking the day great.
text:
Career day at North
We had an amazing day learning about various careers. North staff would like to give a special thank you to the men and women who took the time to speak to the students. We would also like to thank North teachers, Darci Harrison, Lacy Suslee, and Emily Chumley for their help in marking the day great.

post_text: Senior Carter Sabol is now the all-time leading scorer for boys basketball at NHS and Montgomery County! Congratulations to Carter! The picture, provided by NokoPhoto, shows Carter with Coach Kimbro and Mike Havera. Mike, 1997 NHS graduate, had held the scoring record with 1859 points. 🔴⚫️🏀 #NOKOPROUD
